{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Wafer","content":["Line 2 baking trays (40 x 35 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Place spelt or wheat grain and sugar into mixing bowl and mill <nobr>1 min\/speed 9<\/nobr>.","Add butter, vanilla, cocoa and salt and mix <nobr>6 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add flour and knead <nobr>1 min\/<\/nobr>, or until dough has come together. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Transfer dough onto a lightly floured silicone bread mat or work surface and knead into a smooth disc shape. Wrap dough in silicone mat or plastic wrap and place into the freezer to chill (approx. 1 hour).","Preheat oven to 180°C.","Once dough has chilled, roll out between silicone bread mat and a sheet of baking paper, or between two sheets of baking paper, to 0.5 cm thickness. Then, using a cooking cutter (5 cm), cut dough into approx. 45 rounds and place onto prepared baking trays.","Bake for 8 minutes (180°C). Transfer biscuits onto a wire rack and allow to cool completely."]},{"title":"Mint layer","content":["Place all mint layer ingredients into mixing bowl and blend <nobr>30 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then knead <nobr>30 sec\/<\/nobr>.","Lightly dust silicone bread mat or work surface with extra icing sugar, then transfer dough onto it. Shape dough into a thin log (15 cm long, 2 cm wide). Wrap dough in baking paper and place into freezer for 1 hour. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Line 2 freezable containers or trays with baking paper, then spread cooled wafers out onto them.","Remove mint thin dough from freezer and set aside for 2-3 minutes to soften slightly. Once softened, cut into slices (2 mm thick) and place 1 slice of the mint layer on top of each wafer. Transfer wafers back into freezable containers or onto trays, then place back into freezer for 30 minutes."]},{"title":"Chocolate","content":["Place chocolate into mixing bowl and melt <nobr>3 min\/50°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add peppermint oil to taste, then melt for a further <nobr>3 min\/50°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>, or until chocolate has fully melted. Transfer melted chocolate into a ceramic or glass bowl.","Remove wafers from freezer, then working as quickly as possible so the chocolate doesn't harden, use 2 forks to gently dip each wafer into the chocolate.","Place coated wafers back into containers or onto trays, then place into refrigerator for 2 hours to set.","Serve immediately or transfer into a sealable container and place in refrigerator to store until ready to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Wafer","content":["85 g spelt grain","110 g raw sugar","250 g unsalted butter, cut into cubes","1 tsp vanilla bean paste","85 g cocoa powder","1 pinch sea salt","180 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting"]},{"title":"Mint layer","content":["260 g icing sugar, plus extra for dusting","25 g unsalted butter","25 g evaporated milk","¼ tsp peppermint oil (food grade)"]},{"title":"Chocolate","content":["1000 g dark chocolate chips","3 - 5 drops peppermint oil (food grade), to taste (optional)"]}],"id":"r89706","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-pAqgabtCqXo\/XZWqyQbkutI\/AAAAAAAAfdU\/2M-jRXFBWygJfljwVr9FLZAtTrE7ZweRwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_UYxhHSAzaUpedqmA.png","title":"Chocolate mint thins","publishedAt":"2015-12-14T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2.5 g","fat":"12 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"26 g","calories":"921 kJ \/ 219 kcal"},"usefulItems":"2 baking trays (40 x 35 cm), baking paper, plastic wrap, silicone bread mat, rolling pin, round cookie cutter (5 cm), 2 freezable containers or trays, ceramic or glass bowl, wire rack, freezer, oven, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["<strong>After dinner mints<\/strong>: omit the wafer component of the recipe and reduce dark chocolate chips in step 13 to 350-400 g. Proceed as per recipe."],"basicInfo":["medium","40m","2h 30m","45 pieces"]}